
'''Renting/exchanging your own music and movies via the I Let You exchange.'''

URL = http://www.iletyou.com/

"I Let You (Iletyou.com) is a pretty bold adventure in user generated content. It basically lets anyone set up a Netflix type video and game rental store for free, using their own stock and charging their own prices. The idea is that many people have huge collections of discs which they can profit from, either via renting out or exchanging within the community. It’s brave all right, if only because many pundits predict that on-demand movies and games will eventually render assets on physical media obsolete."
(http://www.redferret.net/?p=8430)


